Source: packetsonde-agent
Section: net
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Bill Nash <bill@billn.net>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), cmake (>= 3.20),
 libpcap-dev, libhiredis-dev, libssl-dev, pkg-config
Standards-Version: 4.6.0

Package: packetsonde-agent
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, libpcap0.8
Recommends: libhiredis0.14, libssl3
Suggests: redis-server
Description: Passive network sensor with honeypot and flow generation
 PacketSonde is a privilege-separated network agent that discovers
 hosts via ARP/NDP/DHCP/mDNS/LLDP, generates NetFlow-style traffic
 summaries, runs traceroutes, and operates honeypot trap ports.
 Designed for inline bridge deployment as a passive network tap.
